****************************************************************************************************
Setup instructions
Open a terminal in the project folder.
Run: npm install
Set environment variables by copying .env.example to .env.development or .env.test and fill values.


Note:npx runs binaries from your local node_modules/.bin folder without needing a global install. 
Playwright provides its CLI (playwright) this way, so npx is the right tool.
****************************************************************************************************

1 Install npm first by npm install, to verify version npm --v
2 Install typescript globally by npm install -g typescript, to verify version tsc --v
3 Set env variables in 3 fiels according to the need
  3.1 .env.example to .env.development or .env.test

4.Package.json
  ðŸ“¦ What is package.json?
      Itâ€™s the manifest file for a Node.js project.
      Contains metadata: project name, version, scripts, dependencies, etc.
      Required if you want to install packages with npm or yarn.
  >npm init
     This starts an interactive wizard asking questions (name, version, description, entry point, etc.).
     At the end, it generates a package.json.   
  or
  > npm init -y
     Instantly creates a package.json with sensible defaults.
    
5.Update package.json with needed scripts and dependencies,(Node Module is getting created now)
  > npm install  -->to install all dependencies
  > npm install express -> to install specific node packagae
  > npm install --save-dev playwright  --> to speifc dev only not require in prod,packahe.json categorzie accordingly
  > npm install -g typescript --> install globally
  Note:To uninstall npm uninstall dotenv zod

6.Set up TSConfig file by running command npx tsc --init(In my machine, Some error occured)
  Hence installed typescript globally -->  npm install -g typescript
   and called tsc --init

7.Create .eslintrc.cjs
    Itâ€™s the configuration file for ESLint, the tool that checks your code for style and quality issues.
    The .cjs extension means itâ€™s written as a CommonJS module (using module.exports), instead of JSON or ES Modules.

    ESLint supports multiple config formats:
    .eslintrc.json â†’ JSON format
    .eslintrc.js â†’ JavaScript (ESM or CommonJS depending on project)
    .eslintrc.cjs â†’ Explicitly CommonJS (safe when "type": "module" is set in package.json) WE use it here!!

8.Create prettierrc file:
    ðŸŽ¨ What is .prettierrc?
    .prettierrc is a configuration file for Prettier, a code formatter.
    It tells Prettier how you want your code styled (indentation, quotes, trailing commas, etc.).
    Instead of passing options every time you run Prettier, you save them in .
    prettierrc so they apply automatically.

